items.abstract: <jats:title>Abstract</jats:title><jats:p>Analytical results for the spatial dependence of the correlation functions for all meson excitations in perturbative Quantum Chromodynamics, the lowest order, are calculated. The meson screening mass is obtained as a large distance limit of the correlation function. Our analysis leads to a better understanding of the excitations of Quark Gluon Plasma at sufficiently large temperatures and may be of relevance for future numerical calculations with fully interacting Quantum Chromodynamics.</jats:p>
title: Meson correlation function and screening mass in thermal QCD

items.abstract: <jats:p>An apparatus is described which allows continuous recording of water uptake by a plant. The elements of this apparatus serve at the same time for measurement of root pressure. The size of the recorded portion of uptaken water and of weeping sap excreted by the plant root can be regulated.</jats:p>
title: Automatic measurement of water uptake and weeping sap excretion by root system
